Global Dysprosium Compounds Market Insights
Dysprosium Compounds Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.3 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Dysprosium Compounds Market Overview
The global Dysprosium Compounds market has been experiencing substantial growth over the past few years, driven by increasing demand for rare earth elements in various high-tech applications. In 2024, the market size is valued at approximately USD 800 million, with projections indicating a steady CAGR of 5.5% from 2025 to 2030. Dysprosium compounds, primarily used in the production of magnets, batteries, and phosphors, have been crucial in the development of electronics, renewable energy technologies, and electric vehicles. The growth in these sectors has led to an increasing need for high-performance materials, contributing to market expansion.

